quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  11,9,"And if We let man taste mercy from us, and thereafter withdraw it from him, verily he is despairing, blaspheming"
  11,10,"And if We let him taste favour after harm hath touched him, he saith: the ills have departed from me; verily he becometh elated, boastful"
  11,11,Not so are those who persevere and do righteous works. Those! theirs shall be forgivness and a great hire
  11,12,"So hapoy thou mayest abandon part of that hich hath been revealed unto thee, and thy breast is straitened thereby, because they say: wherefore hath not a treasure been sent down unto him, or an angel come with him! Thou art but a warner, and of everything Allah is the Trustee"
  11,13,"Or say they: he hath fabricated it? Say thou: bring ye then ten Surahs the like thereunto fabricated, and call whomsoever ye can beside Allah, if ye say sooth"
  11,14,"Then if they respond you not, know that it hath been sent down only with the Knowledge of Allah, and that there is no god but he; are ye Muslims then"
  11,15,"Whosoever desireth the life of the world and the adornment thereof, We shall repay them in full their works therein, and in it they shall not be defrauded"
  11,16,"These are they for whom there is not in the Hereafter save the Fire; to naught shall come that which they have performed, and vain is that which they have been working"
  11,17,"Is he like unto him who resteth upon an evidence from His Lord, so and there rehearseth it a witness from Him And before it was the Book of Musa, a pattern and a mercy; these believe therein; and whosoever of the sects disbelieveth therein, the Fire is his promised place. Be then thou not in dubitation thereof, verily it is the truth from thy Lord, yet most of the mankind believe not"
  11,18,"And who doth greater wrong than he who fabricateth a lie against Allah! these shall be set before their Lord, and the witnesses shall say; these are they who lied against their Lord. Lo! the curse of Allah shall fall on the wrong-doers"
  11,19,"Who hinder others from the way of Allah and would seek crockedness therein, and they: in the Hereafter they are disbelievers"
  11,20,"These could not escape on the earth, nor could there be for them protectors against Allah; doubled shall be the torment for them; they were notable to hearken, nor would they be clear sighted"
  11,21,"These are they who have lost their souls, and hath strayed from them that which they have been fabricating"
  11,22,Undoubtedly they! in the Hereafter they shall be the greatest losers
  11,23,"Verily those who believed and worked righteous works and humbled themselves before their Lord--they shall be the fellows of the Garden: therein they shall be abiders"
  11,24,"The likeness of the two parties is as the blind and deaf, and the seeing and hearing. Are the twain equal in likeness? Admonished are ye not then"